        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 20 at 3:29PM CST by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 329 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 4 miles north of Umbarger to 4 miles southeast
of Buffalo Lake to 10 miles southwest of Happy. Movement was
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Canyon, Mescalero Park, Bushland, Buffalo Lake, Umbarger,
and Timbercreek Canyon.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 27 between mile markers 91 and 120.
Interstate 40 between mile markers 57 and 65.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
